properties.Name: InterestRateIndex
properties.Description:
A regularly published rate, independent of the lending institution, that measures the prevailing cost of funds, and is used periodically with the margin to set AML accrual rates.

The index is the measure of interest rate changes that the lender uses to decide how much the interest rate on an adjustable rate mortgage will change

Ex:
- LIBOR
- Prime Rate
- Treasury Index
- 11th District Cost Of Funds
- Cost Of Funds Index

Columns.Name: InterestRateIndexId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of an Interest Rate Index.

Columns.Name: InterestRateIndexName
Columns.Description: The name of an Interest Rate Index.

Columns.Name: InterestRateIndexDescription
Columns.Description: The description of an Interest Rate Index.
